  "title": "Talent Acquisition Executive – Entry Level",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Summary:</strong></u></p><ul><li><p>Gross Salary: $3500 - $5000 (Based on performance)</p></li><li><p>Location: Jurong East</p></li><li><p>Working hours: Monday – Friday (Office Hours - Flexi)</p></li><li><p>Attractive Benefits + Incentives</p></li></ul><p><u><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><ul><li><p>Screen and evaluate applications and resumes to identify candidates aligned with role requirements and client expectations</p></li><li><p>Coordinate and schedule interviews with candidates and clients, ensuring a smooth, professional, and positive recruitment experience</p></li><li><p>Build and maintain strong candidate relationships through clear communication on role expectations and recruitment timelines</p></li><li><p>Provide timely updates and feedback to candidates throughout the application process to enhance candidate experience</p></li><li><p>Partner closely with the Business Development team to provide guidance on recruitment best practices and effective candidate selection strategies</p></li><li><p>Support internal stakeholders to ensure alignment between client needs and candidate profiles</p></li><li><p>Ensure recruitment activities comply with TAFEP guidelines and relevant employment regulations</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate and up-to-date recruitment records, candidate tracking, and hiring metrics for reporting and analysis</p></li><li><p>Gather and analyse feedback from candidates and new hires to continuously improve recruitment processes and employer branding efforts</p></li><li><p>Contribute to initiatives that strengthen the organisation’s talent attraction and market positioning</p></li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><p>• Candidates should be results-driven, with a commitment to meeting the company’s sales targets<br /></p><p><br />Applicants who possess relevant experience for the above responsibilities are most welcome to apply. If you do not possess the above experience, your application will still be considered on individual merits and you may be contacted for other opportunities.</p><p>Please submit your updated resume in MS Words format by using the <strong>APPLY NOW BUTTON.</strong></p><p>By submitting your personal data and/or resume, you give consent to collection, use and disclosure of your personal data and/or resume by the company (or its agent) for the purpose of the processing and administration by the company relating to this job application.</p><p>**We regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates would be notified.</p><p>https://www.mci.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/MCI-Job-Applicant-Data-Protection-Notice.pdf</p><p>Ng Zi Ying</p><p>CEI Registration Number: R25154197</p><p>EA Licence No: 06C2859 (MCI Career Services Pte Ltd)</p>",
